## 4. Database Schema & Entity Relationships

```mermaid
erDiagram
    Transaction {
        String id PK
        DateTime date
        String type "income | expense"
        String category
        String description
        Float amount
        String reference "payroll:uuid | invoice:uuid"
        Boolean deleted
        DateTime createdAt
        DateTime updatedAt
    }

    PayrollEntry {
        String id PK
        String employeeName
        String role
        Float salary
        Float bonus
        Float deductions
        Float netPay
        String payPeriod "YYYY-MM"
        String status "pending | paid"
        DateTime paidAt
        String transactionId FK
        Boolean deleted
    }

    Quote {
        String id PK
        String clientName
        String description
        String items "JSON [{name,qty,unitPrice}]"
        Float totalAmount
        String status "draft|sent|accepted|rejected|converted"
        DateTime validUntil
        String invoiceId FK
        Boolean deleted
    }

    Invoice {
        String id PK
        String clientName
        String description
        String items "JSON [{name,qty,unitPrice}]"
        Float totalAmount
        String status "unpaid | paid | overdue"
        DateTime dueDate
        DateTime paidAt
        String quoteId FK
        String transactionId FK
        Boolean deleted
    }

    ProfitSnapshot {
        String id PK
        String period "YYYY-MM or YYYY-Q1"
        Float totalIncome
        Float totalExpense
        Float netProfit
        String metadata "JSON"
        DateTime createdAt
    }

    PayrollEntry ||--o| Transaction : "generates (on pay)"
    Invoice ||--o| Transaction : "generates (on pay)"
    Quote ||--o| Invoice : "converts to"
```

> ⚠️ **`items` field is a JSON string** in both `Quote` and `Invoice`. Routes parse/stringify on every read/write. No Prisma relation is used — it's a serialized array.

---

## 5. Automated Business Logic Flows

These are the critical cross-module side-effects that keep all data consistent.

### 5a. Payroll Payment Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (Payroll.jsx)
    participant API as POST /api/payroll/:id/pay
    participant DB as SQLite via Prisma

    FE->>API: POST /api/payroll/{id}/pay
    API->>DB: Find PayrollEntry (must be "pending")
    API->>DB: CREATE Transaction {type:"expense", category:"Payroll", amount: netPay, reference: "payroll:{id}"}
    API->>DB: UPDATE PayrollEntry {status:"paid", paidAt: now, transactionId: tx.id}
    API-->>FE: { payroll, transaction }
    Note over DB: netPay = salary + bonus - deductions
```

### 5b. Invoice Payment Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (QuotesInvoices.jsx)
    participant API as POST /api/invoices/:id/pay
    participant DB as SQLite via Prisma

    FE->>API: POST /api/invoices/{id}/pay
    API->>DB: Find Invoice (must NOT be "paid")
    API->>DB: CREATE Transaction {type:"income", category:"Invoice Payment", amount: totalAmount, reference: "invoice:{id}"}
    API->>DB: UPDATE Invoice {status:"paid", paidAt: now, transactionId: tx.id}
    API-->>FE: { invoice, transaction }
```

### 5c. Quote → Invoice Conversion Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (QuotesInvoices.jsx)
    participant API as POST /api/quotes/:id/convert
    participant DB as SQLite via Prisma

    FE->>API: POST /api/quotes/{id}/convert { dueDate? }
    API->>DB: Find Quote (must NOT be "converted")
    API->>DB: CREATE Invoice {clientName, description, items, totalAmount, dueDate, quoteId: quote.id}
    API->>DB: UPDATE Quote {status:"converted", invoiceId: invoice.id}
    API-->>FE: { quote, invoice }
    Note over DB: dueDate defaults to +30 days if not provided
```

---

## 6. Data Flow: Dashboard Aggregation

```mermaid
graph LR
    DB1[("Transaction\ntable")] -->|"all non-deleted rows"| RPT
    DB2[("PayrollEntry\ntable")] -->|"count / pending count"| RPT
    DB3[("Quote table")] -->|"count"| RPT
    DB4[("Invoice table")] -->|"count / unpaid count"| RPT

    RPT["GET /api/reports/dashboard"]

    RPT --> SUM["summary KPIs\ntotalIncome, totalExpense,\nnetProfit, counts"]
    RPT --> MBD["monthlyBreakdown[]\n{month, income, expense, profit}"]
    RPT --> CBD["categoryBreakdown[]\n{category, income, expense}"]
    RPT --> RTX["recentTransactions[5]"]

    SUM --> DASH["Dashboard.jsx\n(Recharts bar + pie charts)"]
    MBD --> DASH
    CBD --> DASH
    RTX --> DASH
```

