## 7. Key Design Decisions & Gotchas

| # | Decision | Implication |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Soft deletes everywhere** | All tables have `deleted: Boolean`. All queries must include `where: { deleted: false }`. Never use hard DELETE on financial records. |
| 2 | **Transaction as ledger** | Every financial action (payroll payment, invoice payment) creates a `Transaction` row. The `reference` field links back using `"payroll:{uuid}"` or `"invoice:{uuid}"` string format. |
| 3 | **Items stored as JSON string** | `Quote.items` and `Invoice.items` are `String` in Prisma (SQLite limitation). Routes always `JSON.parse()` on read and `JSON.stringify()` on write. |
| 4 | **No auth layer** | This is a demo system. There is no authentication or authorization middleware. |
| 5 | **ProfitSnapshot is manual** | Snapshots are explicitly POSTed by a user action — they are NOT auto-generated. They capture a point-in-time view of a period. |
| 6 | **Payroll ≠ Employee model** | There is no persistent `Employee` model. Each `PayrollEntry` embeds `employeeName` and `role` directly as strings. |
| 7 | **No input validation library** | Routes do manual `parseFloat()` and string checks. No Zod/Joi schema validation. |
| 8 | **Vite proxy not configured** | Frontend calls `http://localhost:3001` directly via axios base URL. Both servers must run simultaneously during development. |

---

## 8. Running Locally

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["1. cd backend\nnpm install"] --> B["2. npx prisma db push\n(create SQLite schema)"]
    B --> C["3. node prisma/seed.js\n(load sample data)"]
    C --> D["4. node index.js\nAPI on :3001"]
    E["5. cd frontend\nnpm install"] --> F["6. npm run dev\nUI on :5173"]
    D --> G["✅ System Ready"]
    F --> G
```

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd temple-finance/backend
npm install
npm run db:push      # prisma db push
npm run seed         # node prisma/seed.js
npm run dev          # node index.js → http://localhost:3001

# Terminal 2 — Frontend
cd temple-finance/frontend
npm install
npm run dev          # vite → http://localhost:5173
```

